-- Thailand Equity Movers: Chai Watana, PTT Exploration, Srivichai
-- B y   A n u c h i t   N g u y e n
-- 2012-06-18T09:54:22Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-06-18/chai-watana-rayong-purifier-srivichai-thailand-equity-preview.html
Shares of the following companies
had unusual moves in Thailand  trading . Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of the close in Bangkok.  The  SET Index (SET)  fell 0.2 percent to 1,163.41.  Chai Watana Tannery Pcl (CWT)  , a producer of leather
seats for automobiles, advanced 1 percent to 2.10 baht. The
company’s revenue may rise to 1.2 billion baht ($38 million) in
2012, Thai-language Kao Hoon reported, citing Managing Director
Weerapon Chaiteerath. The company may build a plant in
 Indonesia , the newspaper said. Weerapon wasn’t available for
comment after a call to his office.  PTT Exploration & Production Pcl (PTTEP)  , the nation’s
only publicly traded oil explorer, dropped 1.4 percent to 172
baht. Oil for July delivery declined as much as 0.4 percent to
$83.66 a barrel in  New York .  Srivichai Vejvivat Pcl (VIH)  , a hospital operator, slid
2.6 percent to 3.06 baht, the lowest close since June 7.
Investors are required to pay cash upfront before placing orders
to buy the company’s shares, the Thai exchange said in a
statement.  To contact the reporter on this story:
